.TH "qmi_send_message" 9 "qmi_send_message" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
qmi_send_message \- send a QMI message
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" qmi_send_message
.BI "(struct qmi_handle *qmi "  ","
.BI "struct sockaddr_qrtr *sq "  ","
.BI "struct qmi_txn *txn "  ","
.BI "int type "  ","
.BI "int msg_id "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ","
.BI "struct qmi_elem_info *ei "  ","
.BI "const void *c_struct "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "qmi" 12
QMI client handle
.IP "sq" 12
destination sockaddr
.IP "txn" 12
transaction object to use for the message
.IP "type" 12
type of message to send
.IP "msg_id" 12
message id
.IP "len" 12
max length of the QMI message
.IP "ei" 12
QMI message description
.IP "c_struct" 12
object to be encoded
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function encodes \fIc_struct\fP using \fIei\fP into a message of type \fItype\fP,
with \fImsg_id\fP and \fItxn\fP into a buffer of maximum size \fIlen\fP, and sends this to
\fIsq\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, negative errno on failure.
